---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="A-Frame Cabin Builder Ontario | PCM Homes" description="Custom A-frame cabin builder in Ontario. PCM Homes builds year-round A-frame houses in Muskoka, Kawartha Lakes & cottage country. 9 years experience.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section data-hero="dark" class="relative min-h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/images/projects/image00011.jpeg"
        alt="Custom A-frame cabin built by PCM Homes in Ontario"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/60 via-black/50 to-black/70"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center text-white pt-24">
      <p class="section-label text-white/80 mb-4">Custom Builds</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-display font-medium mb-6">
        A-Frame Cabin <span class="italic">Builder</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Building A-frame cabins and year-round homes across Ontario's cottage country. From design to keys in hand.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Get a Quote</span>
        </a>
        <a href="tel:9057161939" class="btn-secondary border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
          Call (905) 716-1939
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is an A-Frame Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Basics</p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
        What is an <span class="italic">A-Frame?</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="divider mb-10"></div>

      <div class="prose-pcm text-lg">
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>An A-frame is a building style where the roof extends from the foundation to the peak on both sides, forming the shape of the letter "A."</strong> There are no traditional walls—the roof is the wall. This creates dramatic interior spaces with soaring ceilings and a distinctive look that's been popular in cottage country since the 1950s.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          A-frames work particularly well on sloped or uneven lots. The simple foundation requirements and efficient design mean they're often more affordable than traditional builds. And they handle Ontario winters exceptionally well—the steep roof sheds snow naturally, reducing maintenance and structural stress.
        </p>
        <p>
          We've built A-frames as weekend getaways and as full-time family homes. With proper insulation and modern building techniques, an A-frame can be just as comfortable year-round as any custom home.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why A-Frames Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Benefits</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Why Build an <span class="italic">A-Frame?</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Lower Building Costs</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Simpler structure means less material and labor. A-frames typically cost 15-25% less than traditional builds of similar square footage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M3 15a4 4 0 004 4h9a5 5 0 10-.1-9.999 5.002 5.002 0 10-9.78 2.096A4.001 4.001 0 003 15z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Handles Snow Naturally</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">The steep 60-degree roof pitch sheds snow on its own. No raking, no worrying about snow load. Built for Ontario winters.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Energy Efficient</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Smaller footprint and less exterior surface area means less heat loss. We build to R-40+ insulation levels for year-round comfort.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Faster Construction</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Most A-frames go from foundation to move-in in 3-5 months. Less complex framing means quicker build times.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Timeless Style</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">A-frames never go out of fashion. The dramatic interior spaces with floor-to-ceiling windows create stunning living areas.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Low Maintenance</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Metal roofing sheds debris naturally. No gutters to clean. Less exterior siding to maintain. More time enjoying, less time fixing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our A-Frame Services -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label text-[var(--color-timber)] mb-4">What We Build</p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display mb-6">
            A-Frame <span class="italic">Services</span>
          </h2>
          <div class="divider mb-10"></div>

          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div class="flex gap-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-lg">01</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-display mb-2">Custom A-Frame Design</h3>
                <p class="text-white/70">Work with us from scratch or bring your plans. We'll help you optimize for your lot, budget, and how you want to use the space.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-lg">02</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-display mb-2">Permits & Planning</h3>
                <p class="text-white/70">We handle building permits, site plans, and coordinate with the municipality. You shouldn't have to navigate bureaucracy alone.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-lg">03</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-display mb-2">Full Construction</h3>
                <p class="text-white/70">From foundation to finishing touches. We manage every trade and keep you informed every step of the way.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-lg">04</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-display mb-2">Shell or Turnkey</h3>
                <p class="text-white/70">Want to do some work yourself? We can build to lock-up stage and let you finish the interior. Or we handle everything—your choice.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="relative">
          <div class="img-zoom">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00007.jpeg"
              alt="A-frame cabin interior with timber framing"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/5] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 bg-[var(--color-timber)] p-8 text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
            <p class="text-4xl font-display mb-1">9+</p>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium">Years Building<br />in Ontario</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Build Process -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">How We Work</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Our Build <span class="italic">Process</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center mb-8"></div>
        <p class="text-xl text-[var(--color-slate)] max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Here's our promise: you'll always know what's happening with your build. Weekly updates. Phone calls returned the same day. No surprises.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5 gap-8">
        {[
          { step: '01', title: 'Consultation', desc: "We visit your lot, discuss your vision, and give you honest feedback on what's possible within your budget." },
          { step: '02', title: 'Design & Quote', desc: "Detailed plans and a fixed-price quote. You'll know exactly what you're getting and what it costs." },
          { step: '03', title: 'Permits', desc: "We handle the paperwork. Building permits, site plans, septic approvals—all of it." },
          { step: '04', title: 'Construction', desc: "Weekly updates with photos. We answer every call. You're never left wondering." },
          { step: '05', title: 'Handover', desc: 'Final walkthrough, all documentation, and our 2-year workmanship warranty.' },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-4 border-2 border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">{item.step}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gallery Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Our Work</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          A-Frame <span class="italic">Projects</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="group relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="img-zoom aspect-[4/3]">
            <img src="/images/projects/image00009.jpeg" alt="A-frame cabin exterior" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/20 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 flex items-end p-6">
            <div class="text-white">
              <p class="font-display text-lg">Cottage Country A-Frame</p>
              <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">Kawartha Lakes</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="img-zoom aspect-[4/3]">
            <img src="/images/projects/image00003.jpeg" alt="A-frame interior living space" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/20 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 flex items-end p-6">
            <div class="text-white">
              <p class="font-display text-lg">Modern A-Frame Interior</p>
              <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">Year-Round Home</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="group relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="img-zoom aspect-[4/3]">
            <img src="/images/projects/image00002.jpeg" alt="A-frame with large windows" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/20 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 flex items-end p-6">
            <div class="text-white">
              <p class="font-display text-lg">Open Concept Design</p>
              <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">Muskoka Region</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Common Questions</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          A-Frame <span class="italic">FAQ</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">How much does it cost to build an A-frame cabin in Ontario?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>Expect $200 to $400 per square foot for a complete, turnkey A-frame in 2024. A modest 800 sq ft cabin runs $160,000-$320,000. A larger 1,500 sq ft year-round home is typically $300,000-$600,000. The range depends on site access, finishes, and whether you're building on serviced land or need well and septic. We provide detailed quotes after seeing your lot—no surprises down the road.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">How long does it take to build an A-frame?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>Most A-frames take 3 to 5 months from foundation pour to move-in. Permits add 4-8 weeks before construction starts, depending on the municipality. Simpler designs on accessible lots can be faster. Remote locations with challenging access take longer. We'll give you a realistic timeline in our initial consultation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">Can an A-frame be a year-round home?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>Absolutely. We build A-frames to R-40+ insulation standards with modern HVAC systems, triple-pane windows, and proper air sealing. They're as warm and comfortable as any custom home. Many of our clients live in their A-frames full-time. The key is building it right from the start—retrofit insulation is expensive and never as effective.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">Do A-frames need special permits in Ontario?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>A-frames require the same building permits as any other home in Ontario. You'll need a building permit from the municipality, and possibly septic and conservation authority approvals depending on your lot. Some townships have specific zoning requirements for roof pitch or building height. We handle all the permit applications and know what each municipality requires.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">What size A-frame can I build?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>A-frames range from compact 400 sq ft cabins to spacious 3,000+ sq ft family homes. Most of our builds fall between 800 and 2,000 sq ft. The steep roofline limits usable floor space on upper levels, so larger A-frames often incorporate dormers, extensions, or a more traditional second floor. We'll help you figure out what size makes sense for your needs and lot.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">Are A-frames hard to furnish?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>The sloped walls do require some creativity. Tall bookshelves and standard dressers don't work against A-frame walls. But built-in storage, platform beds, and low furniture work beautifully. Most clients find the dramatic ceiling height and open feel more than compensates for the furniture constraints. We can incorporate built-ins during construction if that's a priority.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] pr-8">Where do you build A-frames?</h3>
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-timber)] transform group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
            <p>We build throughout Muskoka, Kawartha Lakes, Durham Region, York Region, and the GTA. Most of our A-frame projects are in cottage country—Huntsville, Bracebridge, Haliburton, the Kawarthas. But we've also built A-frames as primary residences closer to the city. If you've got a lot in Ontario, we can probably build on it.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[var(--color-cream)] border-t border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-center">
        <div>
